From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Matthew Vance <yinzara@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 13 Nov 2025 18:35:00 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] Export coexistence functions for native HCI mode

Export wsm_ble_msg_coexist_start() and wsm_ble_msg_coexist_stop() functions
for CONFIG_WIFI_BT_COMB mode (native HCI with WiFiBLEComb firmware).

Previously these functions were only exported when CONFIG_ATBM_BLE_ADV_COEXIST
was defined. This caused "Unknown symbol" errors when the driver tried to call
these functions from native HCI mode code.

Split the #ifdef block to only export the coexist_start/stop functions for both
modes, while keeping wsm_ble_msg_set_adv_data() and wsm_ble_indication() only
for CONFIG_ATBM_BLE_ADV_COEXIST mode (as they use functions not available in
native HCI mode).

This allows the automatic coexistence management code (patch 0010) to call
these firmware control functions during BLE connection lifecycle events.
---
 hal_apollo/wsm.c | 8 +++++---
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/hal_apollo/wsm.c b/hal_apollo/wsm.c
index 063dae4..e3cbad4 100644
--- a/hal_apollo/wsm.c
+++ b/hal_apollo/wsm.c
@@ -3727,9 +3727,9 @@ int wsm_phy_read_reg_bit_u32(struct atbm_common *hw_priv, const wsm_regval_bit *
 nomem:
 	return -ENOMEM;
 }
-	
 
-#ifdef CONFIG_ATBM_BLE_ADV_COEXIST
+
+#if defined(CONFIG_ATBM_BLE_ADV_COEXIST) || defined(CONFIG_WIFI_BT_COMB)
 int wsm_ble_msg_coexist_start(struct atbm_common *hw_priv, const struct wsm_ble_msg_coex_start *arg,
 										int if_id)
 {
@@ -3788,7 +3788,9 @@ nomem:
 	return -ENOMEM;
 
 }
+#endif /* CONFIG_ATBM_BLE_ADV_COEXIST || CONFIG_WIFI_BT_COMB */
 
+#ifdef CONFIG_ATBM_BLE_ADV_COEXIST
 int wsm_ble_msg_set_adv_data(struct atbm_common *hw_priv, const struct wsm_ble_msg_adv_data *arg,
 										int if_id)
 {
@@ -3855,7 +3857,7 @@ underflow:
 	return 0;
 }
 
-#endif
+#endif /* CONFIG_ATBM_BLE_ADV_COEXIST */
 #ifdef CONFIG_ATBM_BLE
 int wsm_ble_xmit(struct atbm_common *hw_priv,u8 *xmit,size_t len)
 {
